    {
      "description": "Maret internally weighs her options: compliance means exposing her secret to the System, possibly being taken for study; flight means abandoning her life and Theo, becoming a hunted fugitive. Neither path is safe.",
      "characters": ["Maret Halsey"],
      "kind": "interiority",
      "requiredPayoffs": []
    },
    {
      "description": "She asks Cassel for until the next morning to arrange her guild affairs, hoping to buy time. Cassel agrees, but emphasizes that the interrogation must begin by noon—no extensions. He gives a final warning: the city guard has been notified to watch all exits from the Scribal Quarter.",
      "characters": ["Maret Halsey", "Lucius Cassel"],
      "kind": "dialogue",
      "requiredPayoffs": [
        { "fact_id": "interrogation-schedule", "payoff_beat": 11 },
        { "fact_id": "guard-watching", "payoff_beat": 11 }
      ]
    },
    {
      "description": "Cassel stands, collects the folder, and leaves without another word. The tavern's noise slowly returns to normal, but Maret feels the eyes of some patrons lingering on her. Theo puts a hand on her arm, asking if she's okay.",
      "characters": ["Lucius Cassel", "Maret Halsey", "Theo Marlow"],
      "kind": "action",
      "requiredPayoffs": []
    },
    {
      "description": "Theo expresses his concern and offers to help, saying he can watch her back or act as a witness. Maret feels torn—she knows she can't explain the truth, but she appreciates his loyalty. She deflects weakly.",
      "characters": ["Theo Marlow", "Maret Halsey"],
      "kind": "dialogue",
      "requiredPayoffs": []
    },
    {
      "description": "Alone with her thoughts after Theo leaves, Maret decides she will not flee. She will face the interrogation, but she will prepare—gather evidence, perhaps hide her true logs. A quiet resolve settles over her, tempered by fear. The chapter ends with her staring at the summons on the table.",
